SUMMARY:Master's Programs Application Walkthrough & Q&A: Environmental\, 
 Natural Resources & Energy Law
DESCRIPTION:Applying to graduate law programs doesn't have to feel overwh
 elming. Join Tess Jacobson\, Assistant Director of Lewis &amp\; Clark Law
  School's Environmental\, Natural Resources &amp\; Energy Law Programs\, 
 for an interactive walkthrough of the application process.  This session 
 will cover both the Master of Studies in Law (MSL) for professionals with
  a bachelor's degree and the Master of Laws (LLM) for attorneys and law g
 raduates. It's an opportunity to connect directly with program leadership
 \, ask questions\, and gain guidance as you prepare your application.  In
  this session\, you will:Walk through each step of the application proces
 s  Learn what materials are required and how to strengthen your submissio
 n  Get tips for writing a strong personal statement  Learn about scholars
 hip opportunities and eligibility  Ask questions and receive guidance in 
 real time    Whether you're just beginning the application process or pre
 paring to submit\, this session will give you the clarity and confidence 
 to move forward with applying to the MSL or LLM program.Register Here for
  Zoom link (https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/register/7417732605359/WN_x2V
 MXhuUSI-4bj36LoasgQ#/registration)
