SUMMARY:Belonging Cornerstone Webinar ŌĆō Guiding Students in Vocation an
 d Calling
DESCRIPTION:Through our campus's participation in the CIC Belong communit
 y\, all faculty and staff are invited to attend at no cost. Can't make th
 e live event but still want to engage with the discussion? You can still 
 register (https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_oDMzzhXqSq6O_UJErzs
 BgA#/registration) and the recording will be emailed to you following the
  session!Register here! (https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_oDMz
 zhXqSq6O_UJErzsBgA#/registration)Webinar Description: Conversations about
  vocation and calling are deeply shaped by the students we serve. Their i
 dentities\, experiences\, and sense of belonging influence how they under
 stand purpose\, possibility\, and the paths they imagine for their lives.
  This webinar explores how vocation conversations shift across different 
 student populations and campus contexts.  Join us on March 31 to hear fro
 m college and university leaders reflect on how questions of difference\,
  inclusion\, and belonging intersect with the ways students engage ideas 
 of vocation and calling. Drawing on their work with students in varied in
 stitutional settings\, speakers will share insights into how educators ca
 n foster meaningful vocation conversations that resonate with the diverse
  communities they serve.Featuring:Christine Jeske\, Wheaton College (IL) 
  Jason Mahn\, Augustana College  Monica Smith\, University of Richmond
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Through our campus's participation in t
 he CIC Belong community\, all faculty and staff are invited to attend at 
