SUMMARY:Call for Papers: 2026 Dorothy Berkson Writing Award in Gender Stu
 dies
DESCRIPTION:17th Annual Dorothy Berkson Writing Award in Gender Studies  
 &#160\;  This award recognizes written achievement (e.g.\, scholarly essa
 ys\, research projects\, creative non-fiction\, fiction\, poetry\, or pla
 ywriting) focused on gender and authored by a senior.  A monetary prize a
 ccompanies the award.  The award winners will present their papers at a r
 eception on April 18\, 2025 (https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/even
 t/354223-2024-reception-for-dorothy-berkson-writing-award) that celebrate
 s their work. The presentation will be recorded for archival purposes. Th
 ese awards are given in memory of Dorothy Berkson\, professor emerita of 
 English who taught at Lewis &amp\; Clark from 1981 until her retirement i
 n 2004.Submissions due by 5 p.m.Friday\, March 21\, 2025  &#160\;Submissi
 ons may come from any field of study as long as gender is central to the 
 work. The author must be a graduating senior in 24-25. Most often the wor
 k will be produced in the senior year\, but outstanding work from one's j
 unior year will also be considered.  Submissions (maximum 5\,000 words) m
 ust be accompanied by a faculty recommendation that provides context for 
 the work and speaks to its merits.  Awardees will be determined by a facu
 lty committee  Student submissions use this link (https://forms.gle/SshBH
 XoezQbmZS4R6) to a Google form  Faculty recommendations use this link (ht
 tps://forms.gle/NtqhfPnCQJyuYam36) to a Google form    &#160\;Professor B
 erkson was a presenter in Lewis &amp\; Clark's first Gender Studies Sympo
 sium. For the gender studies minor\, she designed a course titled Gender 
 and Aesthetic Expression\, which she continued to teach for many years.  
 &#160\;Info about past awardees (https://www.lclark.edu/departments/gende
 r_studies/dorothy-berkson-writing-award/dorthy-berkson-award-archive/)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<h2>  17th Annual Dorothy Berkson Writing Aw
 ard in Gender Studies</h2><p style="text-align: left\;">  &#160\;</p><p s
 tyle="text-align: left\;">  This award recognizes written achievement (e.
 g.\, scholarly essays\, research projects\, creative non-fiction\, fictio
 n\, poetry\, or playwriting) focused on gender and authored by a senior.<
 /p><p style="text-align: left\;">  A monetary prize accompanies the award
 .</p><p>  The award winners will present their papers at a <strong><a hre
 f="https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/event/354223-2024-reception-fo
 r-dorothy-berkson-writing-award" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reception
  on April 18\, 2025</a></strong> that celebrates their work. The presenta
 tion will be recorded for archival purposes. These awards are given in me
 mory of Dorothy Berkson\, professor emerita of English who taught at Lewi
 s &amp\; Clark from 1981 until her retirement in 2004.</p><h4 style="text
 -align: center\;"><strong>Submissions due by 5 p.m.</strong></h4><h4 styl
 e="text-align: center\;"><strong>Friday\, March 21\, 2025</strong></h4><p
 >  &#160\;</p><ul><li>Submissions may come from any field of study as lon
 g as gender is central to the work. The author must be a graduating senio
 r in 24-25. Most often the work will be produced in the senior year\, but
  outstanding work from one's junior year will also be considered.  </li><
 /ul><ul><li>Submissions (maximum 5\,000 words) must be accompanied by a f
 aculty recommendation that provides context for the work and speaks to it
 s merits.  </li></ul><ul><li>Awardees will be determined by a faculty com
 mittee  </li></ul><ul><li><a href="https://forms.gle/SshBHXoezQbmZS4R6">S
 tudent submissions use this link</a> to a Google form  </li></ul><ul><li>
 <a href="https://forms.gle/NtqhfPnCQJyuYam36">Faculty recommendations use
  this link</a> to a Google form  </li></ul><p>  &#160\;</p><p><em><pictur
 e class="lw_image lw_image52922 lw_align_left"><source type="image/webp" 
 srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/72/width/150/heigh
 t/214/52922_dorothy_berkson.webp 2x" data-origin="responsive"/><source ty
 pe="image/jpeg" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/72
 /width/150/height/214/52922_dorothy_berkson.rev.1429734859.jpg 2x" data-o
 rigin="responsive"/>
<picture>
<img alt="" width="150" height="214" data-decoration=
 "true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/72/width/150/height/214
 /52922_dorothy_berkson.rev.1429734859.jpg" title="Berkson photo 2" srcset
 ="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/72/width/150/height/214/
 52922_dorothy_berkson.rev.1429734859.jpg 2x" data-max-w="394" data-max-h=
 "562" loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/>
</picture></picture>Professor Berkson w
 as a presenter in Lewis &amp\; Clark's first Gender Studies Symposium. Fo
 r the gender studies minor\, she designed a course titled Gender and Aest
 hetic Expression\, which she continued to teach for many years.</em></p><
 p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong><a href="https://www.lclark.edu/departments/gen
 der_studies/dorothy-berkson-writing-award/dorthy-berkson-award-archive/">
 Info about past awardees</a></strong></p>
