BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T163000
LOCATION:JR Howard 202
SUMMARY:The Heretic and The Historian: Simon Magus\, Early Christianity\,
  and the Problem of Historiography\; Shaily Patel (Virginia Tech)
DESCRIPTION:Please join us to learn about this fascinating story where he
 resy and history overlap!  You can learn more about Dr. Shaily Patel's wo
 rk by visiting her faculty page (https://liberalarts.vt.edu/departments-a
 nd-schools/department-of-religion-and-culture/faculty/shaily-patel.html)!
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Please join us to learn about this fasc
 inating story where heresy and history overlap!</p><p>  You can learn mor
 e about Dr. Shaily Patel's work by visiting her <a href="https://liberala
 rts.vt.edu/departments-and-schools/department-of-religion-and-culture/fac
 ulty/shaily-patel.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">faculty page</a>!<
 /p>
UID:20260403T223000Z-387323@www.lclark.edu
DTSTAMP:20260317T141337Z
URL:https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/event/387323-the-heretic-and-
 the-historian-simon-magus-early
LAST-MODIFIED:20260317T212721Z
ATTACH:https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/82/width/80/height/80/crop/1
 /src_region/0,24,454,478/112458_image.rev.1773781978.jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-TYPE:events
X-LIVEWHALE-ID:387323
X-LIVEWHALE-TIMEZONE:America/Los_Angeles
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE:https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/82/width/80/heigh
 t/80/crop/1/src_region/0\,24\,454\,478/112458_image.rev.1773781978.jpg
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE-CAPTION:Professor Shaily Patel
X-LIVEWHALE-COST:Free
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  Elizabeth A. Clark writes\, "A major but often
  unacknowledged problem with historical knowing is that the past is not a
 n object of sense perception that can be experienced empirically in the p
 resent." In other words\, historians' knowledge of the past is hampered b
 y our inability to directly experience it\; we can only partially reconst
 ruct it from fragmentary and even contradictory evidence. But modern hist
 orians are not the only ones who had to contend with the problem of incom
 plete evidence. Ancient Christian writers did too. In this lecture\, Dr. 
 Shaily PatelŌĆōassistant professor of early Christianity in the Departmen
 t of Religion and Culture at Virginia TechŌĆō offers a brief survey of on
 e of early Christianity's most-reviled arch-heretics\, Simon Magus\, in o
 rder to demonstrate the various strategies ancient authors used to supply
  missing information and develop their own orthodoxies in the process.\n<
 /p>
X-LIVEWHALE-TAGS:History Major|History Minor|Religious Studies Major|Reli
 gious Studies Minor|religious studies|send-to-undergraduate|student event
 |student
END:VEVENT
