LOCATION:Smith Hall
SUMMARY:Leadership and Advocacy with Matthew Bergman JD '86
DESCRIPTION:Are you an advocate? Do you have courage? Are you looking for
  inspiration?&#160\;  Join us for an exclusive conversation with Matt Ber
 gman (https://www.lclark.edu/live/profiles/12091-matthew-bergman-jd-89)\,
  the Lewis &amp\; Clark Law alumnus who founded The Social Media Victims 
 Law Center and is representing over 1\,700 plaintiffs against social medi
 a and tech giants. Matt is an advocate\, law professor\, philanthropist\,
  and a member of Lewis &amp\; Clark's Board of Trustees who is motivated 
 by the quote "If you save one life\, you save the world."  Read more abou
 t Matt Bergmans work here (https://time.com/7334078/matthew-bergman-socia
 l-media-victims-lawsuits/).&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<div>  Are you an advocate? Do you have cour
 age? Are you looking for inspiration?&#160\;</div><div></div><div>  Join 
 us for an exclusive conversation with <span class="il"><a href="https://w
 ww.lclark.edu/live/profiles/12091-matthew-bergman-jd-89">Matt Bergman</a>
 </span>\, the Lewis &amp\; Clark Law alumnus who founded The Social Media
  Victims Law Center and is representing over 1\,700 plaintiffs against so
 cial media and tech giants. <span class="il">Matt</span> is an advocate\,
  law professor\, philanthropist\, and a member of Lewis &amp\; Clark's Bo
 ard of Trustees who is motivated by the quote "If you save one life\, you
  save the world."</div><div></div><div>  Read more about Matt Bergmans wo
 rk <a href="https://time.com/7334078/matthew-bergman-social-media-victims
 -lawsuits/">here</a>.&#160\;</div><div></div>
