DESCRIPTION:Joyce Ann Harpole '79 exemplified professionalism with her de
 light for life and the balance she achieved between her legal career\, fa
 mily\, friends\, and community before she passed away at the age of 42. T
 he Harpole Awards (https://law.lclark.edu/offices/alumni/harpole_awards/)
  recognize both an Oregon attorney and a current Lewis &amp\; Clark Law S
 chool student who personify Joyce's sense of professionalism and dedicati
 on to the pursuit of justice while maintaining a life balance that distin
 guished her within her personal and professional communities. The law stu
 dent also receives a scholarship for their final year of law school.  You
  are invited to celebrate the 28th Joyce Ann Harpole Awards Ceremony &amp
 \; Reception on Wednesday\, April 8th from 4-6 p.m. at Stoel Rives (addre
 ss: 760 SW 9th Ave.\, Ste. 3000\, Portland\, OR). Our attorney award reci
 pient is Ani E. Yardumian\, an attorney who specializes in abuse and negl
 ect\, and our student scholarship recipient has not yet been announced.&#
 160\;  Please note that the ceremony will begin in-person at 4pm. Please 
 RSVP here (https://engage.lclark.edu/register/?id=beb031c0-8278-4dbe-92ac
 -03b9889f5acb).
