X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  <strong>Alicia Kirkland Coachman</strong> grad
 uated with a computer science &amp\; mathematics degree in 2016. While at
  Lewis &amp\; Clark Alicia spent two summers as an intern through the Rog
 ers Program: one summer at OHSU in a neuroscience lab and one summer deve
 loping a student cybersecurity exercise with Jens. Since graduating she h
 as primarily worked as a DevOps Engineer with a focus on building AWS inf
 rastructure based on security and compliance frameworks such as SOCII and
  FedRamp. She is currently working as a Security Automation Engineer at N
 ew Relic.\n</p>
