SUMMARY:Auditions for Fall 2026 MainStage Musical
DESCRIPTION:Come audition for the Fall MainStage Musical:  Natasha\, Pier
 re &amp\; the Great Comet of 1812Music Auditions: 10-2:30pm in Seitz Loun
 ge in Evans Music CenterDance Auditions: 3-5pm in Fir Acres BlackboxThe T
 heatre &amp\; Dance and Music Departments will hold pre-auditions this sp
 ring for a few roles in the Fall 2026 MainStage Musical.&#160\; (Audition
 s will be held again in Fall 2026 for roles that are not filled.) Sign up
  on the Call Board in Fir Acres Theatre.The music audition will consist o
 f three elements:A range check (warmup)  An unaccompanied folk song or po
 p song of your choosing  A song from the list below that corresponds to t
 he character you are interested in    The following song suggestions for 
 each character draw from a wide range of musicals and pop/rock music\, ch
 osen to align with the characters' complexities\, emotions\, and the voca
 l demands of the roles. The list below is certainly not meant to be the o
 nly songs we want to hear\, but ideas about the type of song.You are expe
 cted to bring sheet music for your song from this list. If you need help 
 finding the sheet music please contact Prof. Cox (lc21-1459@lclark.edu (m
 ailto:lc21-1459@lclark.edu)) or Sue McBerry (mcberry@lclark.edu (mailto:m
 cberry@lclark.edu))  Pierre Bezukhov"Anthem" from Chess    Natasha Rostov
 a"I Feel Pretty" from West Side Story    Andrey Bolkonsky"Johanna (Repris
 e)" from Sweeney Todd    Anatole Kuragin"Left Behind" from Spring Awakeni
 ng    H├®l├©ne Bezukhova"The Ladies Who Lunch" from Company    Marya D"Se
 nd in the Clowns" from A Little Night Music    Sonya"On My Own" from Les 
 Mis├®rables    Dolokhov"Stars" from Les Mis├®rables    Balaga"Sit Down\, 
 You're Rockin' the Boat" from Guys and Dolls    Mary Bolkonskaya"I Dreame
 d a Dream" from Les Mis├®rables    Old Prince Bolkonsky"Edelweiss" from T
 he Sound of Music
