 ana\, The Tower\, the pieces tell a story of liberation. This performance
  will be live streamed here. (https://vimeo.com/event/4079258)Parking at 
 Lewis &amp\; Clark - For events in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Chap
 el\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion\, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswold
 \, Lower Griswold\, or Fir Acres Lots (see: campus map (https://www.lclar
 k.edu/live/files/7676-campus-map)).Parking permits are required during th
 e academic year between Monday through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see th
 e Visiting Campus page (https://www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transpor
 tation/visitor_parking/) for additional details. For weekday events befor
 e 7pm\, visitors may purchase day passes online (https://lclark.t2hosted.
 com/Account/Portal) or via QR codes posted in all major parking lots.
