DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T173000
SUMMARY:2026 Distinguished Business Law Graduate Reception
DESCRIPTION:Shawn Filippi (https://www.lclark.edu/live/profiles/14032-sha
 wn-filippi-99) JD'99 has spent over 25 years advising boards of directors
 \, CEOs\, and executive teams through complex legal\, regulatory\, govern
 ance\, compliance\, and business issues. She currently serves as Head of 
 Policy Engagement and Advocacy at the National Society for Corporate Gove
 rnance\, where she also chairs the national Small- and Mid-Cap Public Com
 pany Committee. In those roles she engages in advocacy work with the SEC 
 and legislative\, regulatory\, judicial\, and other policy-making and sta
 ndard-setting entities on behalf of public and complex private companies 
 nationally.                                  Previously\, Shawn spent ove
 r a decade as Vice President\, Chief Compliance Officer\, and Corporate S
 ecretary of NW Natural Holdings and NW Natural\, and prior to that\, held
  a variety of legal leadership positions supporting all aspects of those 
 same businesses. Before that\, she was an attorney at Stoel Rives LLP\, f
 ocusing her practice on corporate\, securities and finance\, and mergers 
 and acquisitions. She started her career clerking in the Special Litigati
 on Unit of Oregon Department of Justice.                                 
  Despite the demands of her career\, Shawn found time to give back and su
 pport Lewis &amp\; Clark Law School. She currently serves on two leadersh
 ip boards for the school: the Board of Visitors and the Center for Busine
 ss Law and Leadership. Relatively shortly after her graduation in 1999\, 
 she led the Alumni Board as president from 2001 - 2006. In addition to he
 r work at Lewis &amp\; Clark boards\, she currently serves as a board mem
 ber of the KARES Foundation\, a national nonprofit focused on an ultra-ra
 re neurodevelopmental genetic condition\, and is a board member of the Pa
 cific Northwest Chapter of the Society for Corporate Governance and serve
 s on the Advisory Counsel for the PDX Corporate Counsel Forums.
