LOCATION:Beth Miller Lounge (2nd Floor Fowler)
SUMMARY:First Generation Table Talks
DESCRIPTION:Hello First-Generation* Community and those interested!  We a
 re excited to have you join us for our monthly First-Gen Table Talks!Purp
 ose of Event:Be in community and network with other First-Generation stud
 ents\, staff\, and faculty    Gain navigational skills by asking 'adultin
 g 101' questions (examples could include: how to buy a car\, what is a cr
 edit score\, how to make the most of college\, what am I doing here?! The
 re is no such thing as a silly question!)    Enjoy a free community meal 
    Spring 2026 First-Gen Table Talk:          Wednesday\, April 22nd\, 20
 26\, from 3:30-5 pm\, Beth Miller Lounge (2nd Floor of Fowler)        Spe
 cial Guest: TBD          Table Talk Logistics:RSVP here (https://forms.gl
 e/RfKheHghnzFEjomp9) to let us know if you plan to attend! We'll send you
  an email reminder leading up to our event!          Food will be provide
 d - supplies will be limited\, so come when you can! Please feel free to 
 bring your own lunch as well.          These events are meant to be infor
 mal\; please feel free to come/go as your schedule allows. No need to sta
 y the entire time.              Our table talk series is hosted by First-
 Gen staff member Kamariah Hammonds (IME\, Assistant Director)      Questi
 ons? Email us at IME (multicultural@lclark.edu).  *Like any identity\, id
 entifying a clear definition is always challenging\, as each individual i
 s complex and unique. Defining a First-Generation College Student is no d
 ifferent and can be complicated. IME welcomes any student who believes th
 ey would benefit from our First-Generation Programs. We encourage you to 
 reach out to IME if you have questions about defining who is First-Genera
 tion and/or if you would like to share more about your experience!
