SUMMARY:Music Colloquium: Dr. Kerry McCarthy
DESCRIPTION:Tudor Singers on the Road  We hear a lot about Renaissance co
 mposers\, but Dr. Kerry McCarthy will talk about the people who actually 
 sang their music and brought it to life\, sometimes in quite challenging 
 circumstances\, and how touring as a musician with Henry VIII wasn't all 
 that different from touring with Taylor Swift!Kerry McCarthy is a musicia
 n and author who has published widely on the English Renaissance\, includ
 ing award-winning new biographies of the composers William Byrd and Thoma
 s Tallis. She is now writing her fourth book\, an exploration of the live
 s of professional singers in Tudor England. She lives in Portland\, where
  she was born and raised.  &#160\;Parking at Lewis &amp\; Clark - For eve
 nts in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion
 \, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswold\, Lower Griswold\, or Fir A
 cres Lots (see: campus map (https://www.lclark.edu/live/files/7676-campus
 -map)).Parking permits are required during the academic year between Mond
 ay through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see the Visiting Campus page (http
 s://www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transportation/visitor_parking/) for
  additional details. For weekday events before 7pm\, visitors may purchas
 e day passes online (https://lclark.t2hosted.com/Account/Portal) or via Q
 R codes posted in all major parking lots.
