 an development\, trauma-informed healing and wellness\, and client-center
 ed therapy rooted in compassion and unconditional positive regard. She ha
 s specialized training in trauma-informed counseling\, mindfulness\, and 
 body-based therapies. Julianna is registered with Yoga Alliance as RYT 50
 0-hr and is excited by the collective considerations of how we can embrac
 e ancient practices from other cultures with ethical\, conscious care. Sh
 e teaches graduate classes as an adjunct faculty member at the Lewis &amp
