SUMMARY:International Aquaculture Law & Policy Symposium
DESCRIPTION:Presented by the Center for Animal Law Studies in collaborati
 on with Aquatic Life Institute and the Multispecies Collective\, the Symp
 osium will bring together experts\, scholars\, and practitioners to discu
 ss key issues and emerging trends in the rapidly evolving field of indust
 rial animal aquaculture law and policy. The day will end with a call to a
 ction to support a collaborative and strategic approach to challenging gl
 obal industrial aquaculture.  Full details regarding the schedule\, speak
 ers\, and registration will be coming soon. Learn more about the event he
 re (https://law.lclark.edu/live/news/57638-save-the-date-for-the-internat
 ional-aquaculture). The Symposium follows the Multispecies Collective PhD
  Workshop (June 2) and the UK Animal Law Conference (June 3-4). Mark your
  calendars for an incredible week of animal law in Birmingham!  For quest
 ions about the Symposium\, please contact cals@lclark.edu (mailto:cals@lc
 lark.edu).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p dir="ltr">  Presented by the Center for A
 nimal Law Studies in collaboration with Aquatic Life Institute and the Mu
 ltispecies Collective\, the <span class="il">Symposium</span> will bring 
 together experts\, scholars\, and practitioners to discuss key issues and
  emerging trends in the rapidly evolving field of industrial animal aquac
 ulture law and policy. The day will end with a call to action to support 
 a collaborative and strategic approach to challenging global industrial a
 quaculture.</p><p dir="ltr">  Full details regarding the schedule\, speak
 ers\, and registration will be coming soon. Learn more about the event <a
  href="https://law.lclark.edu/live/news/57638-save-the-date-for-the-inter
 national-aquaculture" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl
 ="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://law.lclark.edu/live/news/57638-sav
 e-the-date-for-the-international-aquaculture&amp\;source=gmail&amp\;ust=1
 772634897892000&amp\;usg=AOvVaw04TG5cgIlFJv3n8V9oB-QP">here</a>. The <spa
 n class="il">Symposium</span> follows the Multispecies Collective PhD Wor
 kshop (June 2) and the UK Animal Law Conference (June 3-4). Mark your cal
 endars for an incredible week of animal law in Birmingham!</p><p dir="ltr
 ">  For questions about the <span class="il">Symposium</span>\, please co
 ntact <a href="mailto:cals@lclark.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cal
 s@lclark.edu</a>.</p>
