DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T170000
LOCATION:Online
SUMMARY:Trauma-Informed Breathwork for Nervous System Regulation in Clini
 cal Practice (Online)
DESCRIPTION:This experiential workshop introduces clinicians to trauma-in
 formed breathwork as a practical\, ethical\, and accessible tool for nerv
 ous system regulation in clinical settings.  Grounded in somatic psycholo
 gy\, polyvagal-informed approaches\, and breath-based interventions\, thi
 s training provides clinicians with concrete techniques they can immediat
 ely integrate into their work with clients experiencing anxiety\, trauma-
 related stress\, and nervous system dysregulation.  The workshop is organ
 ized around a four-phase somatic arcŌĆöRoot\, Release\, Integrate\, and E
 mbodyŌĆöwhich offers clinicians a structured framework for understanding 
 how breathwork and somatic interventions can be applied at different stag
 es of trauma recovery.  Participants will learn how to use breathwork for
  stabilization and resourcing\, how to safely support emotional and somat
 ic release\, and how to facilitate integration through gentle parts-based
  and inner childŌĆōinformed practices.  In clinical settings\, this train
 ing emphasizes integration before embodiment\, ensuring safety\, pacing\,
  and nervous system stabilization. This sequencing helps clinicians devel
 op a clear understanding of when and how to use breath-based intervention
 s in an ethical\, trauma-informed\, culturally responsive\, and clinicall
 y sound manner.Following this workshop\, participants will be able to:Des
 cribe how trauma impacts the nervous system and breathing patterns.  Expl
 ain the four phases of somatic trauma recovery: Root\, Release\, Integrat
 e\, and Embody.  Demonstrate at least three trauma-informed breathwork te
 chniques for nervous system regulation.Identify appropriate breath-based 
 interventions based on a client's window of tolerance and readiness.  Int
 egrate breathwork and somatic awareness into existing clinical models.  D
 etails &amp\; RegistrationDate: Thursday\, June 18\, 2026\, 1-5 p.m.\, On
 lineInstructor: Caroline McGrath\, LPC\, NCCDetails: $105\, includes 4 CE
 Us. Alumni and Adjuncts save 20%. $45 GSEC Student Rate.Register Online (
 https://lclark.tfaforms.net/wf1W4MQ?epid=a1aUY000002ULDx)  Limited no-cos
 t registrations for GSEC Clinical Mental Health Supervisors\, Faculty\, a
 nd staff. Email cce@lclark.edu (mailto:cce@lclark.edu).Accessibility: We 
 are committed to making our events accessible to all needs and abilities.
  When registering\, please let us know your access needs. Contact us at 5
 03-768-6040 or cce@lclark.edu (mailto:cce@lclark.edu)&#160\;with question
 s.Please note: Discounted &#x2018\;Student Rate&#x2019\; registrations ar
 e for current students only and do not include continuing education credi
 t (CEU/PDUs)About the InstructorCaroline McGrath\, LPC\, NCC is a License
 d Professional Counselor\, Certified Trauma-Informed Breathwork and Hypno
 Breathwork Facilitator\, Certified Somatic Jungian Coach\, and Certified 
 TRE┬« Provider. She is the founder of Soul of the Lotus┬«\, a practice de
 voted to somatic healing\, depth psychology\, and embodied transformation
 .  Caroline's work integrates clinical counseling\, nervous system regula
 tion\, breathwork\, and inner childŌĆōinformed approaches to support deep
 \, lasting change. She works with college students\, young adults\, and m
 idlife women navigating anxiety\, identity shifts\, and life transitions.
   In addition to her clinical practice\, she leads professional trainings
  for therapists and helping professionals\, as well as retreats and trans
 formational programs for midlife women. Her teaching emphasizes experient
 ial learning\, trauma-informed practice\, and practical somatic tools tha
 t clinicians can confidently integrate into their work.New workshops and 
 trainings are added to our calendar regularly. For the latest on professi
 onal development related to your specific interests\, sign up for our mai
 ling list! (https://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735441)
