 al Supervisor\, having earned her Masters Degree in Professional Mental H
 ealth Counseling from Lewis &amp\; Clark College in 2018. Drawing from an
  integrative feminist approach\, her work is grounded in person-centered 
 values\, emphasizing authentic connection\, and collaborative engagement.
  Her primary clinical focus is supporting clients in navigating identity 
 development\, body politics\, neurodivergence\, emotional codependency\, 
 highly sensitive personalities and other complex emotional experiences.</
 p><p style="line-height: 1.6\;">  In addition to clinical work\, Krystal 
