BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260729T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260729T130000
LOCATION:Online
SUMMARY:AI In Education: Practical\, Ethical\, and Equitable AI Integrati
 on for Educators (Online)
DESCRIPTION:This hands-on workshop is designed for educators who want to 
 confidently integrate AI into teaching\, grading\, and communication whil
 e maintaining academic integrity\, equity\, and human connection.  Partic
 ipants will develop a practical understanding of how generative AI works\
 , how to protect student privacy\, and how to use AI as a productivity an
 d thinking tool rather than a shortcut. Educators will practice prompt de
 sign\, lesson planning\, grading support\, and student-facing AI literacy
  strategies that can be implemented immediately in their own courses.  Ra
 ther than focusing on tools alone\, the workshop centers decision-making\
 , ethics\, and pedagogy so participants leave with confidence\, clear bou
 ndaries\, and ready-to-use instructional materials.  Following this works
 hop\, participants will have an ability to:      Describe how generative 
 AI functions at a practical level and identify key privacy and ethical co
 nsiderations          Write effective prompts to support lesson planning\
 , examples\, and instructional materials          Use AI to design active
  learning activities and grading supports while maintaining instructor vo
 ice          Teach students how to use AI as a learning partner rather th
 an a replacement for thinking    Respond to potential AI misuse using cle
 ar\, restorative\, and documented approaches  Details &amp\; Registration
 Date and Time: Wednesday\, July 29\, 2026\, 9 a.m.-1 p.m\, PT\, OnlinePre
 senter: Jessica BernardsCost and Credits: $105\, includes 4 PDUs. GSEC Al
 umni and Adjuncts save 20%. GSEC Teacher Education Mentors and Supervisor
 s save 20%. $50 GSEC student rate.  Limited no-cost registration availabl
 e for GSEC Faculty and Staff. Email cce@lclark.edu (mailto:cce@lclark.ed)
  with your request to register.Register Online (https://lclark.tfaforms.n
 et/wf1W4MQ?epid=a1aUY000002UxmH)Accessibility: We are committed to making
  our events accessible to all needs and abilities. When registering\, ple
 ase let us know your access needs. Contact us at 503-768-6040 or cce@lcla
 rk.edu (mailto:cce@lclark.edu)&#160\;with questions.Please note: Discount
 ed &#x2018\;Student Rate&#x2019\; registrations are for current students 
 only and do not include continuing education credit (CEU/PDUs)About the P
 resenterJessica Bernards is an award-winning educator\, faculty developme
 nt leader\, and professional learning facilitator with more than 20 years
  of experience supporting teachers\, faculty\, and academic support teams
  across KŌĆō12\, higher education\, and professional learning environment
 s.  She is nationally recognized for designing and leading practical\, eq
 uity-centered professional development focused on teaching\, learning\, a
 nd responsible AI integration.  Jessica is an expert in helping educators
  use AI to support instruction\, assessment\, feedback\, and student lear
 ning without compromising academic integrity or human connection\, and he
 lps translate complex ideas into clear\, classroom-ready practices and fo
 r empowers educators to use AI as a thinking partner rather than a shortc
 ut.  She is currently a Lead Asynchronous Mathematics Instructor &amp\; F
 aculty Consultant at University of Oregon\, and a Mathematics Professor &
 amp\; Faculty Development Leader at Portland Community College.New worksh
 ops and trainings are added to our calendar regularly. For the latest on 
 professional development related to your specific interests\, sign up for
  our mailing list! (https://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735441)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p style="line-height: 1.5\;">  This hands-o
 n workshop is designed for educators who want to confidently integrate AI
  into teaching\, grading\, and communication while maintaining academic i
 ntegrity\, equity\, and human connection.</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;
 ">  Participants will develop a practical understanding of how generative
  AI works\, how to protect student privacy\, and how to use AI as a produ
 ctivity and thinking tool rather than a shortcut. Educators will practice
  prompt design\, lesson planning\, grading support\, and student-facing A
 I literacy strategies that can be implemented immediately in their own co
 urses.</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;">  Rather than focusing on tools a
 lone\, the workshop centers decision-making\, ethics\, and pedagogy so pa
 rticipants leave with confidence\, clear boundaries\, and ready-to-use in
 structional materials.</p><h4>  Following this workshop\, participants wi
 ll have an ability to:</h4><ul><li><p style="line-height: 1.5\;">      De
 scribe how generative AI functions at a practical level and identify key 
 privacy and ethical considerations    </p></li><li><p style="line-height:
  1.5\;">      Write effective prompts to support lesson planning\, exampl
 es\, and instructional materials    </p></li><li><p style="line-height: 1
 .5\;">      Use AI to design active learning activities and grading suppo
 rts while maintaining instructor voice    </p></li><li><p style="line-hei
 ght: 1.5\;">      Teach students how to use AI as a learning partner rath
 er than a replacement for thinking    </p></li><li>Respond to potential A
 I misuse using clear\, restorative\, and documented approaches  </li></ul
 ><hr /><h2><strong>Details &amp\; Registration</strong></h2><p style="lin
 e-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Date and Time:</strong> Wednesday\, July 29\, 20
 26\, 9 a.m.-1 p.m\, PT\, Online</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>
 Presenter:</strong> Jessica Bernards</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><st
 rong>Cost and Credits:</strong> $105\, includes 4 PDUs. GSEC Alumni and A
 djuncts save 20%. GSEC Teacher Education Mentors and Supervisors save 20%
 . $50 GSEC student rate.</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;">  Limited no-co
 st registration available for GSEC Faculty and Staff. Email <a href="mail
 to:cce@lclark.ed">cce@lclark.edu</a> with your request to register.</p><p
  style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong><a class="btn-small-style-1" href="ht
