LOCATION:Online
SUMMARY:Strengthening Support for LGBTQ+ Students in Challenging Times (O
 nline)
DESCRIPTION:With changing and unstable politics\, policies\, and resource
 s\, knowing how to effectively support LGBTQ+ students has become increas
 ingly complicated for educators and adults.  This workshop for school-bas
 ed staff and administrators will ground into best practices in supporting
  LGBTQ+ students\, and will explore practices that can help bring these g
 uidelines into learning spaces.  This will include a review of Oregon's u
 pdated LGBTQ+ Student Success Plan (https://www.oregon.gov/ode/students-a
 nd-family/equity/lgbtq2siastudenteducation/pages/lgbtq2sia--student-succe
 ss-plan.aspx)\, and time spent generating ideas for creative\, innovative
 \, and responsive implementation of the included tools and recommendation
 s.  This workshop provides educators with an opportunity to connect with 
 other supportive adults across the state and address the real impact that
  the complicated political climate has had on each of us as educators\, c
 ommunity members\, and supportive adults. Ultimately\, this workshop will
  work to affirm educators as community change makers\, and reinforce the 
 concept of hope as an ongoing practice within our professions.Following t
 he workshop\, participants will be able to:Understand recent updates to O
 regon's LGBTQ+ Student Success Plan  Name two tools or approaches that th
 ey can add to their practice as educators to increase student inclusion a
 t their school or workplace  Identify personal practices of hope that sup
 port their professional practice as a trusted adult for LGBTQ+ students  
 Event Details &amp\; RegistrationDate and Time: Tuesday\, August 4\, 2026
 \, 10 a.m-12 p.m.\, OnlineInstructor: Carson Varnum\, MEdRegistration: $4
 9\, includes 2 PDUs. GSEC Alumni and Adjuncts save 20%. $20 student rate.
 Current GSEC Supervisors: Free. Email cce@lclark.edu (mailto:cce@lclark.e
 du) to register.Register Online (https://lclark.tfaforms.net/wf1W4MQ?epid
 =a1aUY000002VSJp)Accessibility: We are committed to making our events acc
 essible to all needs and abilities. When registering\, please let us know
  your access needs. Contact us at 503-768-6040 or cce@lclark.edu (mailto:
 cce@lclark.edu)&#160\;with questions.Please note: Discounted &#x2018\;Stu
 dent Rate&#x2019\; registrations are for current students only and do not
  include continuing education credit (CEU/PDUs)About the InstructorCarson
  Varnum\, MEd\, (he/him) is a community builder and educator with an expe
 rtise in sexual health\, sexualities\, peer education\, and community dev
 elopment. Carson specializes in building capacity in sex educators\, crea
 ting sexuality education and leadership development programming for adole
 scents\, and developing programs that center Queer and Trans communities.
  Carson works at Lewis &amp\; Clark Graduate School as TransActives's Hea
 d of Education and Outreach\, where he supports transgender\, non-binary\
 , and other gender expansive youth by strengthening the systems that surr
 ound them. He received his Masters of Education in Human Sexuality from W
 idener University in 2012 and is currently a PhD student in Education and
  Leadership at Pacific University. Carson is a big fan of being on mounta
 ins\, in rivers\, and with friends.&#160\;New workshops and trainings are
  added to our calendar regularly. For the latest on professional developm
 ent related to your specific interests\, sign up for our mailing list! (h
 ttps://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735441)
