DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260813T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260813T100000
LOCATION:Lewis &amp\; Clark Graduate School
SUMMARY:K-8 Vocabulary Instruction that Sticks (In-Person)
DESCRIPTION:Research is clear that early vocabulary experiences directly 
 correlate to later academic achievements\, yet many of our students lack 
 sufficient vocabulary to successfully access grade level content.&#160\; 
  Through this hands-on workshop\, K-8 teachers\, paraeducators\, and scho
 ol leaders will identify high-leverage vocabulary strategies and learn wa
 ys to implement manageable shifts that foster deep\, lasting student lear
 ning.  Utilizing the new Oregon Early Literacy Standards\, the current Ad
 olescent Literacy Standards\, and high quality texts as anchors\, partici
 pants will learn effective and efficient vocabulary teaching methods that
  are rooted in the Science of Reading and the Science of Learning\, and a
 re complementary to any literacy curriculum.&#160\;  Participants will le
 arn to utilize low-lift/high-leverage vocabulary practices that are prove
 n to boost achievement for all students\, with an emphasis on multilingua
 l\, emergent bilingual\, and neurodiverse students.Through this workshop\
 , participants will learn:Why explicitly teaching sounds\, spellings\, me
 anings\, and uses of words in context is vital for a student's overall co
 mprehension  How to model new vocabulary through oral and written languag
 e\, prioritizing comprehensible input for all students  Effective ways to
